  To create his original design, illustrator Craig Frazier arranged paper cutouts into a composition depicting two birds perched on a branch sharing a devoted gaze â€” the space between them forms a heart. He then created a digital file of the artwork and applied shades of blue to the birds, setting them against a yellow background.

  Frazier's previous projects for the Postal Service include the 2003 *Nurturing Love* stamped envelope and the 2005 *Child Health* stamp.

